  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Macadamia  Small-Scale Farmers Development in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project  will  run form January 2019  to  December  2019  the following   development  of macadamia,  setting up  of macadamia  farmers  filed school,  leas farmers to be  trained  by  agronomists  on Good agricultural  practices, support the construction  of storage and drying table.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project intends to improve the production and quality of macadamia nuts and to improve the income of smallholder macadamia farmers and their access to national and international markets. We will support them in the development of small-scale production of macadamia nuts alongside other food, such as beans and soya, and cash crops, including coffee, onions and cabbage
This project    will improve the livelihoods of smallholder farmers living in poor rural areas of the provinces of Muramvya and Kayanza in Burundi.</narrative>
  </description>
